🧭 BLAS Build Notes (macOS, CMake)
🔑 General rules
Always build out-of-source (use build/)
Always clear cache when switching BLAS
Verify linkage after build (otool -L)
Use:
CBLAS for BLAS
Fortran LAPACK (dsyev_) for eigensolvers
⚙️ 1. Build with OpenBLAS (recommended for performance)
✅ Step 1 — Clean
cd build
rm -rf CMakeCache.txt CMakeFiles
✅ Step 2 — Configure
cmake ../Nwpw \
  -DBLA_VENDOR=OpenBLAS \
  -DCMAKE_PREFIX_PATH=$(brew --prefix openblas)
✅ Step 3 — Build
make -j
✅ Step 4 — Verify
otool -L pwdft | grep openblas

Expected:

libopenblas.dylib
⚡ Runtime (IMPORTANT for MPI)
export OPENBLAS_NUM_THREADS=1

👉 Prevents oversubscription with MPI

🧠 Notes
Best performance for your workload (~20% faster)
Handles DGEMM-heavy workloads well
Good default choice
