🔁 Switching between backends

Always do:

rm -rf CMakeCache.txt CMakeFiles

Then reconfigure with the desired backend.

🔬 Sanity checks (important)
1. Confirm external BLAS is used
nm pwdft | egrep "dgemm_|ddot_|dsyev_"

Expected:

U _dgemm_
U _ddot_
U _dsyev_

👉 U = linked externally (good)

2. Confirm NOT using internal BLAS

You should NOT see:

internal BLAS symbols compiled into binary
fallback blas.h implementations
⚠️ Common pitfalls
❌ Wrong line continuation
cmake ../Nwpw \\n ...

👉 WRONG — \\n is literal text

❌ Forgetting cache clean

Leads to:

wrong BLAS backend
inconsistent performance
❌ Mixing MPI + threaded BLAS

Always limit threads:

OPENBLAS_NUM_THREADS=1
VECLIB_MAXIMUM_THREADS=1
🚀 Recommended default

For your workload:

Use OpenBLAS + MPI + 1 thread per rank
